        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> this is the webpage i did my research for my ring</P><P>hrm, guess the page is down, do a few searches on '10th ring war' etc.., most pages just have info up to 9th, only a few pages out there with the strategis for 10th ring war, what i had was a bank setup as following</P><P>1-3spells i would need for this(deflux and DA x 2), then all the commands(if i remember right it was 5) and FD/sit</P><P>i had the lines setup(as suggested by teh guide i read) as follows</P><P>/attack off<BR>/target scout(i forget his name)<BR>/say Garadain to my side!(or whatever teh commands are)<BR>/loc</P><P>now, the way my guild did the war was a bit diff(although this seems to be what most people do nowadays), i would just spam the hotkey that calls all the hereos at once..., for the FULL duration of the war</P><P>it gets annoying but it keeps more heroes alive(and out of trouble with kos people around etc..)</P><P>so about 10min in i removed the /target, and the /loc lines, i think oyu have to have the scout(pet) targeted for the commands to go throgh, its been a while</P><P>wasnt the 1st ring war my (ex)guild tried but it was the 1st we won</P><P>if your running it i suggest posting thoroughly(maps and so forth) well in advance, so when your trackers call for WEST, everyone knows where exactly to go and so on</P><P>its all fine and dandy till you get to teh 3rd wave, at this point it becomes make/break on a per mob lvl baiscally</P><P>and youd be surprised as to how a well tuned raid guild can botch around alot(the main tactic here is tank-mez, 1 tank/cle per giant, everyone else on the MT, if theres no one on a giant, it will kill casters or run for thurg, if theres 2 people on a giant, it dilutes dps, this is hard for poeple to pull off on the fly, esp later on when the mobs start turning 'real'</P><P>if this is your 1st ring war(for your guild) might wanna have a few practice runs in kael arena/tormax bridge(running in wiht a few groups, taking on like 5-6 arena giants at a time, , get people used to the tank-mez principle</P><P>i know, it seems simple, but it falls apart real quick in a ring war</P><P>and lastly, have your narandi strat layed out at hte begining(on my war, it was only the 2nd time they had gotten to narandi, so there was like 5min of trying to sort out tanks/cheal cycles etc..)<BR>if i remember right hes about a vindi(dont remeber if he rampages, tho im pretty sure he flurries), i only came up to see him at the end(i was busy keeping the heros at the falls), but i remember not being able to land any spells, although, i didnt really try much(only had taps/da/zveefers memmed)</P><P>its def a blast, esp if its your 1st, and let me tell oyu, i was shaking like a wee lass</P><P>GL!</P><P>Kriista Silence<BR>Warlock of Veeshan</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103458" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103458</a></font></td>
