 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Morlock</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> hey bonecaster</P><P>i used this link for my ringwar info. i followed the hotkey setup as explained here in the second post.</P><P><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm7.showMessage?topicID=2905.topic" target="_blank">http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm7.showMessage?topicID=2905.topic</a></P><P>only bit of disinformation with this link is that you give your ring and the note to the sentry to start it, not just the note</P><P>our guild did it last week with 53 odd people. 24 lvl 60 and the rest low to mid 50's (its a good day out for the young ones). it got close at the end but with desperate use of the dorfs we prevailed.</P><P>a few points you may want to consider based on my experience of just running ours -</P><P>1. the dorfs spawn dual wielding and don't accept haste masks so the mages don't need to summon any more</P><P>2. STAY OUT OF COMBAT! i am a 60 tank so i charged straight in on a west wave and got aggrod by a giant - because zrelik the scout is your pet he aggrod the giant, it turned and thumped him one which made him summon ALL of the dorfs to his side. this is a pain because the southern dorfs (churn i think) pathed back to their spot past the spearmen so they aggro, get wiped out, damage the spearmen who enter summon mode and it makes a dogs breakfast of the west flank. easiest way is just not to get hit so i spent the rest of the war as a scout. DO NOT call the southern dorfs for reinforcement on the west flank.</P><P>3. i set up the hotkeys called EAST  WEST  SOUTH  CENTRE and ALL IN. the recruits and soldiers are easy enough but the veterans are tough so i needed the dorfs when we were under a lot of pressure. during the final waves i was sitting at the centre line spamming my ALL IN hotkey and being surrounded by tons of dorfs. i would then go to where i was needed spamming the key so the dorf army was mobile. depending on how many dorf flanks you lose (i had lost west and south by this time) you may only need to summon unused dorf flank armies to you.</P><P>4. kill the captain / general / warlords LAST because their death triggers the next wave. have your MA take these with a cleric and kill them slowly while the rest get mopped up THEN kill the wave commander. kill priests first.</P><P>5. have a solid slip group. put them near thurg and they are the last line to stop any runners. if all goes well they will have a boring few hours but 1 giant reaching thurg will screw everything.</P><P>6. setup an admin channel. put yourself, guild commanders and trackers in this channel. trackers can call the spawns and then the commanders can give the orders over the public channel to eliminate confusion. i found it easier to hand over leadership of the guild to 2 of our officers while i scouted around and kept the dorf army in reserve. delegate to people you can trust (i know HoS to be a solid guild so shouldn't be a problem)</P><P>7. have someone keep spamming /ooc /shout to not aggro the giants and train them to thurg. tell them to die and /consent corpse_dragger_01 who can take them to the rezzing station with the slip group. the final waves will probably see lots of deaths so a rez station is a good idea. get this person to handle public relations when idiots bitch about the scion despawning and thurg depopping if you lose <img src=icon_smile_tongue.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>8. sow instead of soe to help minimise lag. it was easy for us because australian time is an empty server but it may be hell for you with tons of people on the raid and the usual GD traffic.</P><P>9. NO DAMAGE SHIELDS - this includes call of earth. if you get hit by a stray spear you'll aggro giants who will begin summoning. you may also aggro dorfs if you get hit by stray arrows.</P><P>10. bring a six pack. we all got drunk and had an excellent time.</P><P>good luck man. i hope you get your ring. i had a great time running the last war especially with my little dorf army running all over the place</P><P>mewkus bloodbath<BR>oggie warlord of southern armada<BR>prexus</P><P> </font></td>
